205.2	Brownian_motion	Brownian motion	Brownian motion (named after the botanist Robert Brown) or pedesis (from Greek: "leaping") is the presumably random drifting of particles suspended in a fluid (a liquid or a gas) or the mathematical model used to describe such random movements, which is often called a particle theory.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/6d/Translational_motion.gif
